ustom_nodes folder.\nType 'cmd' in the Windows address bar and press Enter.\nPaste this command to install the viewer assuming you have\ngit clone https://github.com/HallettVisual/comfyui-GaussianViewer.git\n\nInstall the SHARP node from:\nhttps://github.com/PozzettiAndrea/ComfyUI-Sharp\n\nRestart ComfyUI.\n\nLORA SETUP\n\nDownload the LoRA here:\nhttps://huggingface.co/dx8152/Qwen-Image-Edit-2511-Gaussian-Splash/tree/main\n\nRename the downloaded file FROM:\n高斯泼溅-Sharp.safetensors\n\nRename it TO:\nQwen-Image-Edit-2511-Gaussian-Splash.safetensors\n\nPlace it in your ComfyUI models/loras folder.\n\nWORKFLOW STEPS\n\nLoad Image: Load your base image.\nFirst Pass: Click Generate (Queue Prompt) to create the initial splat.\nAdjust View: A 3D Gaussian Splat will appear. Rotate to your desired angle.\nLock Camera: Click the \"Set Camera\" button in the viewer!\n(If you don't click this, it will keep generating the exact same image)\nFinal Pass: Click Generate again to process with the Qwen Edit LoRA.\n\nPRO TIPS\n\nBypass the KSampler node while adjusting the camera to save time.\nTry using a Smart Crop Inpainting node to isolate the focus area for closeups.\n\nCREDITS & TUTORIALS\n\nModel/LoRA Credit: wuli-DX (dx8152)\nOriginal Node Credit: https://github.com/CarlMarkswx/comfyui-GaussianViewer\nBilibili Tutorial: https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1enrjBMECz/\nYouTube Tutorial: https://youtu.be/9Vyxjty9Qao"],"color":"#432","bgcolor":"#653"},{"id":197,"type":"KSampler","pos":[603.5970612619365,360.0477358578902],"size":[301.7319579777377,483.24224300372134],"flags":{},"order":24,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"localized_name":"model","name":"model","type":"MODEL","link":394},{"localized_name":"positive","name":"positive","type":"CONDITIONING","link":395},{"localized_name":"negative","name":"negative","type":"CONDITIONING","link":396},{"localized_name":"latent_image","name":"latent_image","type":"LATENT","link":407},{"localized_name":"seed","name":"seed","type":"INT","widget":{"name":